,Recommended,227220,8567151,"Posted: 4 January, 2014",all,Elliot Alderson,"Sang-Froid is a terrific game which unfortunately suffers from not being particularly well known. The story won't have you on the edge of your seat but the key players are well written and likeable. As for the gameplay, it's an interesting blend of tower defense and a sort of hack and slash. Defend your buildings from the wolf hordes for as long as your traps hold out and then wade in with axe and rifle to finish the job. It's a terrific concept that consistently feels fresh with new traps and enemies unlocked every so often. Combine fantastic gameplay with two playable characters who play very differently from each other and some basic RPG elements to make the two even more unique and you have a very entertaining, very enjoyable gaming experience."
