,Recommended,227220,10353679,"Posted: 5 June, 2014",all,Wallas,"It's 4 am and I just beat this game. It was worth every moment of my time. Before anything else, you should know that this hasn't got all that much hack 'n slash in it. The combat is more of a fallback or a way to finish opponents wounded by traps. The real meat of the game is in the planning phase, everything else is merely execution. That doesn't mean it's not fun though. The moments before you spring a deadly trap are as tense as the combat that comes after the trap thins the pack (or fumbles miserably). Speaking of traps, there's a pretty good variety of them as well as a fair variety of enemies that are quite distinct from one another. The game has a number of interesting mechanics that set it apart, such as the fear factor and the ability to manipulate your foes via noise and scent. Unfortunately the voice acting and cutscene animations are kind of terrible. The story isn't that great (let's hope it's a set up for a better one in the sequel). Please don't let that put you off, though. This game absolutely deserves your time and the devs your money."
