76561198040485370,Recommended,227220,8870218,"Posted: 27 January, 2014",all,TheCoyote,"Sang-Froid is an impressively complex RTS, with creative, realistic traps that remain grounded in the setting. Every level requires a careful plan, without a detail of the enemy's plan overlooked. The tension is palpable, as timing is everything: will the wolves finish the bait and move on your house before you've finished killing a werewolf clear on the other side of the map? How long do you have before the bonfire goes out and the pack closes in?Set in pre-Confederation Canada, the setting feels real and is well-maintained: every weapon, potion, trap and setpiece fits in the world. Even the prices are accurate to the time (eg. A bullet only costs a penny, and to bless them costs ten cents). Budgeting your money becomes another challenge; saving up for a better gun becomes difficult when you still have to worry about affording your silver bullets and spike traps to survive the next night.As a game, it is quite fun and exciting, but there are some issues with the presentation. The graphics are nothing pretty, but adequate. The music might wear on your nerves, depending on your taste, but like almost everything else, it is accurate to the time. There is one problem that stuck out, and that is the voice acting, which is bad enough that it falls noticably below the standards that every other aspect of the game meets. Despite the obvious setting, the characters do not speak with the proper accent, nor do they acknowledge the severity of the situation in their flat line-reading. My reccomendation would be to turn off the voices, and I'm thankful that the option is provided.Once the voices had been muted, I had a wonderful time with this game."
,Recommended,227220,7352995,"Posted: 10 October, 2013",all,KONOPA_2110,"This sh.it is AWESOME. Every new «mission» is divided into the daytime, when you plan your defence, place the traps, and buy stuff, and the night, when you act, defending your buildings. Between normal and hard choose hard — the game will appear quite difficult, but that's what you came for. Though there are a lot of parameters, traps, items, etc., you'll find yourself well-informed about every new feature, after watching short but informative video tutorials, appearing all along in your adventure. The best thing about this game is that you have to plan (during the day) every your move, and try to keep the sequence of your further acts together in your head (during the night). Meanwhile, it's not just a mind game, where you plan-and-execute... Actually, the «execution» part is made of real action, filled with suddenness, emotional experience and adrenaline.A rare gameplay masterpiece. 92 out of 100."
