76561198045758384,Recommended,227220,10192786,"Posted: 21 May, 2014",all,Ardis,"Very rarely do I write reviews for games but I felt this one deserved it. This game takes several elements from my favorite genres (RPGs, Strategy, Action/Adventure) and puts them all into one very well-done package. The decisions you make when leveling and planning your strategies are tough and have real consequences on the outcome of the game. Often times you are on your toes trying to get from one place to another on the map and the sense of urgency during the nights you are trying to survive is persistent and effective. The story was very interesting and keep me playing. I almost beat this game in one sitting to find out what was happening. It is a unique and dark story line set in the late 1850s and the time period and setting really add to the story being told. Gameplay elements are good, there are a few small bugs but nothing that really got in my way of enjoying the game. The graphics are simple but they work-it is an indie game but deserves way more attention. There are hand-drawn cutscenes from time to time that add to the experience. You will hear several people talk about the music in this game and let me say they are not wrong in stating it is excellent. I loved it so much I tracked down the artists online and will be buying the albums. They are all French so it was a bit of a hunt but the music is so good it didn't bother me. I hope to see a sequel to this at some point. I would highly recommend this game, especially when on sale."
