,Recommended,227220,8459868,"Posted: 31 December, 2013",all,nickwizard,"Sang-Froid - Tales of Werewolves combines tower defense with wilderness survival horror and a little resource management/trade, and achieves this hefty little combo with style and panache.There are some truly original mechanics in the game, such as the ""fear factor"" that pits your own character's fear (or bravado) against that of the blood-hungry beasts of the night - when the werewolves pluck up enough courage, they will attack; this passing of time is represented by a meter on the HUD.  This mechanic can create some really tense moments as you frantically struggle to reload your flintlock rifle, or try to get away to a well booby-trapped spot on the farm before the hairy hordes close in for the kill.From historically accurate weapons and equipment to an easy to access resource management element, there is plenty to keep the player engrossed in many hours of werewolf bashing.  Oh, and did I mention this game has possibly one of the best (and most fitting) soundtracks I've heard?  Great fun, and at the time of posting this review a great price too."
