,Recommended,227220,10570691,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,DeviousBlue,"This game out of Montreal is very fun and satisfying to play. If you can overlook the awful cinematics and lackluster story telling, the game-play is pretty good! A Chapter or ""level"" consists of 2 phases: daytime strategy planning and night time combat.During the day you can visit shops in town to buy or upgrade equipment, consumables and stat modifying accessories. As well as plan your strategy to survive the coming night by setting up various traps, zip lines and build combat influencing objects like fires or shrines. Each one consumes daylight hours and sometimes money too, so it's a balance to survive as efficiently as possible in order to further fund your plan. I recommend playing on ""hard"" though.At night, you dash around your ever expanding forest territory to defend your friends and their homes from unholy wolf creatures. Combat system is simple and imperfect but still pretty fun. Decently designed skill tree to level through as you gain experience. Also some unique mechanics like wind direction potentially ruining your plan by giving away your scent and the degree to which your enemies fear you needing to be managed.Also worth mentioning is the soundtrack, one of it's strongest features. Found myself humming all the music and listening to what I learned was Quebec style folk music that I would have otherwise described as ""Celtic.""  Certainly worth the few dollars currently being asked during the sale, 15 to 30 hrs of fun strategy & third person action despite simple graphics."
,Recommended,227220,10012187,"Posted: 3 May, 2014",all,Ashen Haze,Tower defense meets survivalist.  A very nice change from the standard 3rd person defense game.
76561197991284559,Recommended,227220,8909648,"Posted: 30 January, 2014",all,Pooman,Fresh concept; Solid game overall.  It's a good time!
76561198009574470,Recommended,227220,8926140,"Posted: 31 January, 2014",all,Stª®w¡ñÐ,"PresentationThe game is divided in three forms: The cut-scenes, which are nicely represented by beautiful art in 2D, as if you were reading a book, the strategy part of the game which is represented by a map in which u have a 360 degree view of the terrain u must defend and in which u can zoom in and out and finally the action part, in which you actually put your plan into action.  The action part is cartoonish but still very enjoyable to look at and in 3D.  If you are looking for 'Crysis' graphics, look elsewhere.  It's much more art oriented.  The music is taken from canadian folklore and is quite nice to listen to.  As for the sounds (explosions, beasts roars, axe hits, guns firing,.) they are well executed and add tangibility to the game.GameplayAs mentioned above, this is a mixed game, whereas you play a tower defense game at first and after that you put your plan to execution in a 3rd view action game.  In the strategy part you are presented with a comprehensive map that tells you which creature you are going to fight, their number and their headings, i e where they will attack.  It is there that you have to put up traps to stop them from attacking buildings and thus destroying them or else you fail the scenario.  You have complete control on which traps to use, and where to use them (as long as they are unlocked from progressing in the game).  You are only limited by the in-game mechanics, i e money and action points.The second part is as said putting your plan into execution, and this is done by pressing the 'Start the night' button in the map view.  You then have control of a lumberjack armed with an axe an a rifle and equipped with potions.  This part is rendered in 3D with a 3rd perspective aspect.  The controls are responsive and the animations are well done.  You can view in real time your traps, set them off if needed to and coming to life.  In all my gameplay, i have encountered one bug related to a specific trap, the spike trap.  Sometimes even if i was standing outside the spikes, they would hit me anyways and kill me with the other beasts standing on it.  Othe than that the gameplay is fun and sometimes even scary!ConclusionFor a 6 member studio, this game is remarkably well done.  I encountered no bugs and everything worked as described.  Depending how much time you wanna spend in the strategy map, this game should take between 10 to 20 hours to complete.  The game is not without cons, and personally i have 2.  First one is regarding the resolution.  Maybe the Devs will patch this up but for now the highest resolution is 1080P.  Second con, if they would also patch the icons in the 3D view which are not big enough with higher resolutions.  Other than that i highly recommand this game."
76561197991438190,Recommended,227220,8927781,"Posted: 31 January, 2014",all,Etro,"Awesome little indie game with a beautiful soundtrack.The gameplay is a mix of tactical preparation and action. There's also weapon upgrades and a cool skill tree.I even enjoyed the story, characters and unique setting A LOT.Can't wait for the sequel!"
