76561198043593476,Recommended,227220,8789024,"Posted: 20 January, 2014",all,Novageir,"Sang-Froid appeals to me in a huge way, there is very little that I actually dislike about this game. The game is very creative and also innovative for games in general; adding interesting mechanics and ideas that are difficult to find in any other game!Simple things like having enemies able to fear you, smell you and hear you, make this game stand out from anything else you could find.What I like:- Great progression - The game is constantly adding new mechanics, enemies, traps and weapons, so it never becomes stale.- Planning - Allowing you to set up traps and decide what to defend during the day, and setting the plan in motion at night is a brilliant idea, and feels so rewarding when you accomplish the level.- The Lore - I usually don't pay attention to the setting of the games world, but Sang-Forid makes me care about the folk history, the overall aesthetic to the game is really amazing.- The Music - The music appeals to me in EVERY GODDAMN WAY POSSIBLE, simply fantastic. It is also very fitting for the world it is set in!What I dislike/ could have been improved:- The story/ Dialogue - I am interested in the story, but due to the fact it was made by french developers the translation from French to English can sometimes come off poor or cheesy, not all the dialogue is bad though and most of the voice actors are actually quite good. It is sadly just not as strong as the rest of the game, but the fact that the developers were able to pull it off in the first place is a positive in my opinion!If you haven't guessed it already, I adore this game and would recommend it to anyone and everyone!"
