,Recommended,227220,2051262,"Posted: 22 July, 2013",all,Kale,"I got this for $7.49 during a sale. Warning: This is a indie title. If you can't stand games that are not perfect, turn around now.Gameplay: You play as one of any two brothers that each night fight to defend their cabin as well as other buildings as you progress. Each night you prepare your map from a top down perspective by putting down traps and obstacles to slow down, damage, and/or kill waves of   werewolves and other creatures. During this time you can also travel to the nerby village to buy supplies(a hub of storefronts). Here buy drinks that heal or give you bonus, supplies, and upgrades your weapons(axe and rifle). When you are ready the night begins and you are put into third person to fight each wave.The story/animation/voice acting is what you would expect of a indie game. Not terrible, but not that amazing.If this is for around $5 and don't mind something differen't, give this game a shot. It is one of those gems you never hear about."
