,Recommended,227220,20908682,"Posted: 2 February, 2016",all,Tamerlane,"The game itself has so many flaws ranging from poor voice acting, story to the clunky engine and combat but there's something about it that's so endearing. If you can get past the flaws it's a pretty fun game. The soundtrack has a nice folksy vibe to it.The game is basically a tower defence where you have about 4 buildings(later on) scattered across the map. Your objective is to protect these buildings while eliminating hostile beasts. You can reroute the beasts' paths and set traps along the way. You also have access to an axe, a rifle and a various potions and protective items. These become available for upgrade later on.It can get hectic at times as the game is not very forgiving and you need to maximize the beasts' route into your traps given the limited resources.Very flawed game but it grows on you if you can look past the numerous flaws. It's good enough to kill time on a lazy weekend."
